Package: sysmon
Architecture: amd64 arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Lightweight terminal system monitor for Linux
 sysmon reads CPU, memory, disk, and network metrics directly from the
 Linux /proc filesystem and displays them as a live-updating terminal
 dashboard. It requires no external runtime dependencies and uses no
 shell subprocesses; all data is parsed natively in Go.
 .
 Features:
  - Per-core and aggregate CPU utilisation
  - Memory and swap usage (using MemAvailable, matching free -h)
  - Disk usage via statfs(2) and per-device I/O from /proc/diskstats
  - Per-interface network throughput from /proc/net/dev
  - Configurable refresh interval via -interval flag
